{
  "doc_id": "57132",
  "text": ", and the result in [CITATION_1] is that there is a one-to-one correspondence between wavelet sets E on one side, and sets E which support an orthogonal direct integral decomposition for the representation U w on the other. Since it is known that wavelet sets may be disjoint, it follows in particular that U w may have direct integral decompositions in the sense of Mackey with support on disjoint Borel subsets.",
